The vannal lobe of the fore wing is more or less straight ( Apanteles -like) but it is also fully setose - suggesting this species might better be placed within the genus Dolichogenidea . However, molecular data clusters the species with other Apanteles . The limits of Apanteles and Dolichogenidea have long been controversial (e.g., Mason 1981 ; Achterberg 2003 ;
Fernandez-Triana 2010
) and solving that is beyond the scope of this paper. The species is characterized by all coxae yellow (but not extensive yellow coloration in rest of the body), very short ovipositor (0.4 x as long as metatibia length), and mediotergite 1 3.8-4.0 x as long as wide at posterior margin.
